condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Additional Counterpart Funds | Description :To ensure availability of adequate funds for the Project, theRecipient shall take all measures necessary on its part to secure, by not later than December 31, 2017, an amount of at least ninemillion seven hundred thousand Euros (€ 9,700,000) to assist in financing the Project. |Due Date :31-Dec-2017

Finance Agreement :Australia Co-financing | Description :The Association shall have the right to suspend the Financing if theAustralia Co-financing Agreement fails to enter into effect by 28 February, 2015. | Due Date :28-Feb-2015

Finance Agreement :Establishment of Agribusiness Management Unit | Description :The Recipient shall establish by August 31, 2015,and thereafter maintain at all times during the implementation of the Project, an Agribusiness Management Unit within the MAL,with terms of reference and resources, including qualified and experienced staff in adequate numbers, all satisfactory to theAssociation. | Due Date :31-Aug-2015

Finance Agreement :IFAD Co-financing | Description :The Association shall have the right to suspend the Financing if the IFADCo-financing Agreement has failed to enter into effect by 31 August, 2015. | Due Date :31-Aug-2015

Finance Agreement :Submission of Annual Work Plan and Budget | Description :The Recipient shall prepare and furnish to theAssociation not later than November 30 of each year during the implementation of the Project (or such later date as the Associationmay agree) for the Association's no-objection, an Annual Work Plan and Budget. | Frequency :Yearly
